article.description: Southern Utah turns away North Dakota 77-71
article.headline: Southern Utah turns away North Dakota 77-71
article.linkText: Southern Utah turns away North Dakota 77-71
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Trey Kennedy scored 16 points to lead a balanced offense as Southern Utah snapped a 26-game losing streak and earned its first conference win, 77-71 over North Dakota Thursday. Cal Hanks and Juwan Major both scored 13, and Casey Oliverson added 11 for Southern Utah (2-26, 1-18 Big Sky). It was the first Division I win of the season for the Thunderbirds, and first victory since topping Arizona Christian on Nov 8. Southern Utah led 32-28 at half and stretched the advantage to 61-45 with 6:17 left before a North Dakota rally. North Dakota used a 26-12 run to cut the lead to 73-71 after Jamal Webb's basket with less than 30 seconds to go. But Race Parsons responded with a layup and added two late free throws as the Thunderbirds prevailed. Webb led North Dakota(15-15, 12-8) with 18 points while Aaron Anderson had 14 and Jaron Nash 12.
